2
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,920
So, how do you like my work
of your hair and makeup?

3
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,360
I like it a lot.

4
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:01,680
Come here. Let me take a look.

5
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:05,040
You are the most beautiful bride
I've ever seen.

6
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,880
What's this?
Are you about to cry? Don't you dare!

7
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:11,520
I worked too hard on your makeup
to let it get ruined now.

8
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,160
I'm just too happy.

9
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,120
Got it. Here.

10
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:19,520
Look at the two of us.

11
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,280
It's not like you're doing much better.

12
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,960
Happy wedding, my darling.

13
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,200
In the future, you'll take on many roles.

14
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:32,080
Wife, mother.

15
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:35,560
But to me, you'll always be

16
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:37,880
that happy child who does
whatever her heart desires.

17
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,480
Alright, Fang Ya'en.

18
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:42,200
I'll always be by your side, you know?

19
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,920
And I'll be by yours too.

20
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:46,080
No, be careful!

21
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:51,600
Don't think I don't know. I can tell

22
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:54,240
what Cheng Kairan is thinking.
How do you feel about it?

23
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:00,840
There's really nothing between us.

24
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,000
Besides,

25
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:06,040
I honestly haven't even considered
starting a new relationship.

26
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,600
Is it because of Jiayu?

27
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,800
Not entirely.

28
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,680
To be honest,

29
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:16,560
it just feels really awkward.

30
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,760
Kai used

31
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,320
to like you, right?

32
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:25,320
Yeah? And now suddenly,
he's acting this way toward me.

33
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,480
I just find it really strange.
No. It doesn't feel right.

34
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,320
What kind of mess is this?

35
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,120
It wasn't me he liked.
He took me for someone else.

36
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:36,800
Don't dismiss him
because of such absurd reasons, okay?

37
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,600
Anyway, I'm doing pretty well

38
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:44,080
right now. I just want
to keep things simple and low-key.

39
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,560
But don't overthink it, okay?

40
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,960
Alright.

41
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,880
Today is your big day. I get it.

42
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,200
People…

43
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,200
should still believe in love, right?

44
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:00,320
That's right, Ya'en.

45
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,920
You'll definitely find
the happiness that's meant for you.

46
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:10,040
DOUBLE HAPPINESS

47
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,000
Close the door!

48
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,720
- Ladies, go easy on us!
- Open the door!

49
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,040
Dear ladies, please go easy on us!

50
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,320
If you want to take the bride away,
you'll have to get through us first.

51
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,680
- Listen up for the challenge!
- Challenge set!

52
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:29,160
- Here comes the challenge!
- Challenge set!

53
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,720
You have 20 seconds

54
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,640
to come up with ten
affectionate nicknames for the bride.

55
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,640
- Ready? Go!
- This is way too difficult!

56
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,080
- Why are you in such a hurry?
- Ladies.

57
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,680
Meng.

58
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,680
- Louder!
- Wifey.

59
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,080
Um…

60
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,640
Can I just give you
red envelopes to skip this?

61
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,880
- No!
- No way!

62
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,960
- Affectionate nicknames!
- Beautiful!

63
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,680
- Exactly!
- Gorgeous!

64
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,480
Next question! Change it up!

65
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,240
- Red envelope!
- Hurry!

66
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,560
Wow, that's quite a lot!

67
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,560
Yep!

68
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,880
Now for the second question!

69
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,680
Tell us about your most memorable moment

70
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,960
during your relationship.

71
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,920
I pushed you into getting married!

72
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,480
- You…
- None of your business! I was asking him.

73
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,760
You traitor!

74
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:13,160
Speak.

75
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,120
- Hurry up and think of one!
- Think of one!

76
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,720
Whatever the affectionate nickname is,
as long as it's from you, anything works.

77
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:21,440
You never pressured me into marriage
or chased me relentlessly.

78
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,520
It was I who expressed
my feelings early on.

79
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,360
I said I knew I would
definitely fall in love with you.

80
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,960
So, dear fairies,
is this answer acceptable?

81
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,240
Let us in!

82
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:35,600
The red envelopes are packed full.
I've got money now!

83
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,200
- Right!
- Good!

84
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,200
- Red envelope!
- We want red envelopes!

85
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,240
- We're way too kind!
- Get inside, now! Go!

86
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,680
Go! Red envelope!

87
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:46,240
Red envelope! Ladies!

88
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,960
- Here!
- Grabbing so fast?

89
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,080
They're all gone!

90
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,080
DOUBLE HAPPINESS

91
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:55,400
The bride and groom
will now serve tea to the father.

92
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,480
Dad, have some tea.

93
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:11,680
Dad, please have some tea.

94
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,240
Here, take it.

95
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,280
Thank you, Dad.

96
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,760
Mom.

97
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:31,000
The bride and groom will now serve tea
to the elders from both families.

98
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,240
- Granny, please have some tea.
- Grandma, please have some tea.

99
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,760
Be careful.

100
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:52,080
It's sweet.

101
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,680
Here, this is from Grandma.

102
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:01,520
- Thank you, Granny.
- Wishing you a lifetime of harmony

103
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,320
and an early arrival
of your precious child.

104
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,040
Yes. Make it quick.

105
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,720
- Come here.
- Aunts.

106
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:10,560
Slow down.

107
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,800
- Big Aunt.
- Big Aunt.

108
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,800
May your hearts be forever united.

109
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:24,240
- Middle Aunt.
- Middle Aunt.

110
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,080
May you have great wealth and prosperity.

111
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,360
From now on, all the money
will be managed by our Meng.

112
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,240
- Got it?
- No problem. Absolutely.

113
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,320
Little Aunt.

114
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,160
- Little Aunt.
- What?

115
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,000
- Little Aunt!
- Little Aunt!

116
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:40,640
Here. Be good to our Meng.

117
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,400
May you always
be happy and sweet together.

118
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,360
- Thank you.
- Definitely. Don't worry.

119
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,720
Is that enough? Should we switch
to the Western style now?

120
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,440
- Western style.
- Yes, go change into your outfits.

121
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,560
- Change clothes.
- Go! Hurry!

122
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:55,040
- I'm going to change then.
- Go ahead!

123
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,560
- Go quickly.
- Come here.

124
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:58,760
Granny will hold them for you.

125
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:00,600
- What about that other bag?
- Here's another one!

126
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,160
- Bring it here.
- Take them all.

127
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,040
- Warm them up.
- Hurry up!

128
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,600
DOUBLE HAPPINESS

129
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:37,600
Meng,

130
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,559
live happily with Jinyu.

131
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,520
Jinyu, she's in your hands now.

132
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:47,040
Don't worry, Dad.
I'll definitely take good care of Meng.

133
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,680
- The most beautiful!
- Beautiful!

134
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,640
So beautiful, Meng!

135
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,040
Hurry, look. So gorgeous!

136
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,760
- Beautiful!
- Dear family,

137
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,640
friends, and neighbors,

138
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,000
welcome to the wedding

139
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,720
of Mr. Li Jinyu and Ms. Ye Meng!

140
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:55,520
I'm today's bridesmaid, and I'll also
be serving as your part-time emcee.

141
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,720
And, of course, I am absolutely
the number one witness to this love story.

142
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:03,160
Do you know when I first noticed

143
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,800
the groom had fallen for the bride?

144
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,640
- When was it?
- When?

145
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:09,480
It was after I stunned everyone

146
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,680
with my singing at the Gem gathering.

147
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:14,040
At that time, Ye Meng happened
to be away from Ningsui for something.

148
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,040
My brother sat in the yard reading a book,

149
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:18,760
but he spent the whole afternoon without
turning a single page. Right, Granny?

150
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,160
Yes. Spacing out.

151
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:23,320
He just couldn't focus.
Sat there all alone the entire day.

152
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,280
So, I asked him,

153
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,680
"What's on your mind?"

154
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,960
Ye Meng, you know what my brother said?

155
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,480
Tell it properly.

156
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:33,400
He said, "There's a palace
of memories in my mind.

157
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,520
I want to place you inside,

158
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:38,520
so that whenever
I close my eyes, I can see you."

159
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,600
Qiao Maimai, I didn't say that.

160
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,360
It's pretty much what he meant.

161
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,040
- Nonsense.
- Didn't you say it?

162
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,240
- My brother said he really missed you.
- That's true.

163
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,720
Ye Meng, what I really mean is that vows

164
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,480
and promises aren't what matter most.
But as an outsider, I can see clearly

165
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:01,080
my brother truly, deeply loves you.
He will definitely treat you well.

166
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,640
Right, groom?
It's your turn to say a few words.

167
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:06,320
it's time to tell her your love
and heartfelt affections.

168
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,120
- Come on.
- Say a few words!

169
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,960
- Say a few words, Li Jinyu!
- Say a few words!

170
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,120
I've already…

171
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,760
said so much,

172
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,520
but today…

173
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,840
I want to thank you
for your patience with me.

174
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,480
You once told me

175
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,560
that the world never meant me any harm.

176
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,600
I never believed that before.

177
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,960
But now, I'm learning to believe it,

178
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:41,480
to feel this world,

179
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:45,440
because I've already met my moon.

180
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,360
Ye Meng.

181
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,520
The luckiest thing

182
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,080
in my life has been meeting you.

183
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:59,320
I may not have been
the best partner in the past,

184
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,320
but from now on,

185
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,400
I will strive

186
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,320
to be a worthy husband.

187
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,120
- Good! Worthy!
- Good!

188
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,320
Good!

189
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,600
- Good!
- Good!

190
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:18,240
I believe my brother
will definitely be a good husband.

191
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,880
Now, bride,

192
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,280
do you have anything
you'd like to say to the groom?

193
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:29,960
The first time I met Li Jinyu,

194
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,840
I thought to myself,

195
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:35,560
how could there be someone in this world
who fits my ideal type so perfectly?

196
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,280
I raised him well!

197
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,560
- Such a crush!
- Well done, Granny! Good Granny!

198
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,640
I really feel so lucky

199
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,960
because I quit my job
and still met my crush.

200
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,400
- What?
- But deep down, I've always known.

201
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:54,640
- The one who makes her heart skip.
- I'm an incredibly lucky person

202
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,960
because there are
so many people who love me.

203
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,720
And today,

204
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,240
that circle has grown by one more.

205
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,480
Li Jinyu,

206
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:10,880
from now on,
my family will be your family.

207
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,120
My friends will be your friends.

208
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:16,160
And every bit of love and luck I receive,

209
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,680
I'll share with you.

210
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:25,880
- Good!
- Good!

211
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:30,760
Alright.

212
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,160
Now, it's time

213
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,400
to hand over
to our very own Ms. Dou Juhua.

214
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,320
She's been itching
to grab the mic from me.

215
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,000
- Come on up, Granny!
- Granny Tou!

216
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:40,440
- Let's hear it!
- Granny Tou!

217
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:44,120
I was afraid I'd get too excited

218
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,400
and forget what I wanted to say,

219
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:49,160
so I even prepared
a little notebook last night.

220
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:54,760
Meng, the first time I saw you,

221
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:55,960
I knew right away

222
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:59,320
that you were meant to be
my precious granddaughter-in-law.

223
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,200
Good!

224
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:05,960
- That's what we call fate, isn't it?
- Yes.

225
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:09,160
That's right. You were never getting away.
I knew it the moment I laid eyes on you.

226
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:12,320
So beautiful. Just stunning.

227
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:16,560
I didn't even want to blink.
I just wanted to keep looking at her.

228
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:19,160
So gorgeous. Exactly like that.

229
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,640
Let me tell you, Badou has a few flaws.

230
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,320
He's a bit timid,

231
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,400
tends to worry too much,

232
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,720
and keeps things bottled up.

233
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:34,120
But today, I saw my own grandson

234
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,440
truly become a man of responsibility.
Isn't that right?

235
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,240
- Right!
- Right!

236
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,560
- Right!
- Right!

237
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:43,040
This is also thanks to Meng

238
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,560
for being able to understand him

239
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:48,240
and accept him as he is.
I owe you my thanks.

240
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:53,800
And from now on,
you two must live well together.

241
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,880
If Badou doesn't behave, just tell Granny.

242
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,040
- Alright.
- Right.

243
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:01,720
From now on, Badou, learn from Granny.
Fear nothing, hold nothing back,

244
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:05,160
and speak your mind.
Okay, I've said enough.

245
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,480
Come on,

246
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,920
Meilan, you say something now.

247
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,600
Look at you crying. Is it because
I spoke too well and moved you?

248
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,840
Come on. Say a few words.

249
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,560
- I won't speak.
- Mom, say something.

250
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:17,400
Don't cry. It's a day of celebration.

251
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,440
- I'd like to speak for my family.
- Go ahead.

252
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,560
Actually,

253
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,400
I just have one thing to say.

254
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,760
May you live a long

255
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,680
and happy life together.

256
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:34,960
Jinyu,

257
